A physiological buffer solution (PBS, pH 7.4) containing 50 U/mL lysozyme. The degradation ability of the scaffolds was studied by
incubating the samples in the medium for up to 28 days. The samples were removed at predetermined time intervals followed by washing and drying them in air. The degradation ratio was calculated from the initial weight (Wi) and the weights measured at 28 days (Wd).
Degradation ratio %ð Þ ¼ Wi–Wdð Þ=Wi½ 100;
